13.32	AI_Winter	AI winter	During the Cold War, the US government was particularly interested in the automatic, instant translation of Russian documents and scientific reports. The government aggressively supported efforts at machine translation starting in 1954. At the outset, the researchers were optimistic. Noam Chomsky's new work in grammar was streamlining the translation process and there were "many predictions of imminent 'breakthroughs'".	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/31/Perceptron.svg/300px-Perceptron.svg.png
